      • updateEndpoint

        public void updateEndpoint(CNISeosCallback<java.lang.Void> callback)
        Queries the Seos TSM for updates available for this endpoint. This method is asynchronous and it will launch a background task to do the following:

        1. Process pending server packets from the persistent storage, only applicable if e.g. last Seos TSM communication was unexpectedly interrupted.
        2. Fetch the first available update from the Seos TSM.
        3. Write the update to Seos on the secure element.
        4. Notify the Seos TSM that the update was processed.
        5. Start over from point 2 until the Seos TSM has no more updates.
        Once all those steps are done the callback interface will be notified. If there are no updates for this device in the Seos TSM an exception will be notified to the callback interface with the MobileKeysErrorCode.SERVER_COMMUNICATION_FAILED error code.

        Processing mobile key updates requires the setup process for the Seos application finished. See isEndpointSetupComplete().

        If Seos password protection has been enabled you need to provide the Seos password as input to this method. The isApiPasswordRequired() method can be used to check if Seos is password protected.

        Parameters:
        callback - Interface to call after the operation is completed.

      • setupEndpoint

        public void setupEndpoint(java.lang.String activationCode,
                          CNISeosCallback<java.lang.Void> callback)
        Installs and personalizes the Seos application on current secure element. This is a long running process involving TCP/IP communication with the Seos TSM, so good practice is to make sure the phone has an internet connection before calling this method.
        This method is asynchronous and the provided callback interface will be notified when the operation has finished.
        Parameters:
        activationCode - The activation code given to the user during sign-up. This code is required to secure the processing of setting up Seos. The code is expected in the following format: XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX, where X is alphanumeric.
        callback - Interface to call after the operation is completed.

      • getRoomNumber

        public java.lang.String getRoomNumber()
        Gets room number for available keys. Keep in mind that one key can open multiple doors (common areas, etc.) and Seos can have multiple valid keys at the same time.
        Returns:
        room numbers for available keys
